          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The new data for the  partial  reaction  (g,3n) cross",
                " section on 159Tb were  estimated  on the base of the",
                " experimental (g,2n) reaction  cross section obtained",
                " in  the energy range above the threshold  B3n of the",
                " reaction (g,3n) in  discrepancy  with  the objective",
                " physical data reliability criteria:",
                " F1 =  SIG(g,1n)/SIG(g,Sn),",
                " F2 =  SIG(g,2n)/SIG(g,Sn),",
                " F3 =  SIG(g,3n)/SIG(g,Sn),",
                " where SIG(g,Sn)=SIG(g,1n)+2SIG(g,2n)+3SIG(g,3n)."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "I",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "n accordance with definition:",
                " F1 must be smaller than 1.00;",
                " F2 must be smaller than 0.50;",
                " F3 must be smaller than 0.33."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "A",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "t  energies  above the  (g,3n) reaction threshold  B3n",
                " = 23.66 MeV this  cross   section  was  not  obtained",
                " experimentally  at all but the estimated SIGest(g,3n)",
                " can be naturally  described using  the expression for",
                " the neutron yield reaction cross section:",
                "            SIGexp(g,Sn) = 2SIGexp(g,2n) =",
                "      SIGeval(g,1n)+2SIGeval(g,2n)+3SIGest(g,3n),",
                " where SIGeval(g,1n) and SIGeval(g,2n) were evaluated",
                " using the  experimental-theoretical  method  and the",
                " data reliability criteria F1-3:",
                "The  new data  for (g,3n) cross section  undetermined",
                " before were estimated using the following equation:",
                "   SIGest(g,3n) = 2/3[SIGexp(g,2n)-SIGeval(g,2n)-",
                "                  1/3SIGtheor(g,1n)."
              ]
            }
          ],
